features: ALL-PURPOSE KITCHEN KNIFE – This versatile butcher knife is great for cutting ribs, slicing a pineapple and cutting up cakes and pies. The blade measures 5-3/8 inches and has an overall length of 9-7/8 inches.

STAINLESS STEEL BLADE – The blade on the butcher knife is made from surgical grade, T420 high carbon stainless steel and hand sharpened. The blade is strategically sized so you can effortlessly cut items large and small.

BRUSHED ALUMINUM HANDLE - The handle on the butcher knife is made from permanently cast silver brushed aluminum with a satin finish. This kitchen knife should not be washed in the dishwasher. Handwashing is recommended.

AMERICAN MADE KNIFE – Rada Mfg. Co. is located in Waverly, Iowa and has been manufacturing cutlery in the USA since 1948. Our mission is all about “providing our customers the best value of kitchen knives for their dollar.”
HASSLE-FREE LIFETIME GUARANTEE – We stand by our craftsmanship. Rada Mfg. Co. will replace any product manufactured by our company returned to us due to defects in material or workmanship.
body.description: The Rada Cutlery R106 Stubby Butcher Knife is a versatile kitchen knife that you will find yourself using for a wide variety of kitchen tasks. The 5-3/8 inch blade is sized so you can use this knife on foods big and small. It is ideal for cutting ribs, disjointing poultry, slicing a pineapple or large melon and cutting up cakes and pies. The blade on the butcher knife is made from surgical grade, T420 high carbon stainless steel and hand sharpened creating a razor sharp edge. The hollow ground blade ensures a precision concave surface for maximum edge retention. The handle grip is sized as a traditional butcher knife which will help you control the blade easier. There is also a finger guard for your safety while using the knife. The handle on the butcher knife is made from permanently cast silver brushed aluminum with a satin finish. This kitchen knife should not be washed in the dishwasher. Handwashing is recommended. Rada Mfg. Co. is located in Waverly, Iowa and has been manufacturing cutlery in the USA since 1948. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars After 18 months, still a good knife
reviews.reviewText: I bought this 18 months ago. I use it daily.It came sharp. I've had to hone it a few times to restore the edge, which I have to do with any knife, but I can put a really nice edge on it quickly.So, it came good and with some care, stays sharp and good. It was a good purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great products..have had one for many years..decided to buy another because the first one's tip bent..no fault of the knife....all on me/ these are great kitchen knives and this model is our most used..nothing fancy..all utility..pretty comfortable for a lot of different tasks..buy one!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this knife. It has a razor sharp blade so be careful. I am ready to throw away all my other knives - this is the best! Order one you will not be disappointed. Just do not put in the dishwasher - it will discolor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: For the money Rada knives are exceptional. Very sharp.I have had expensive Cutco knives and Rada for a fraction of the cost holds their own for quality and sharpness.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 25, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I don't see why this knife is rated so highly . Its sharp on first use, but after cutting 3 onions and a tomato , its already not very sharp at all. Way overrated

Forget those $200+ knives and just get yourself of few of these. I'm not a professional chef, just the average joe cooking daily for family. I've had a few different expensive brands and this Rada blows them all out of the water. Its light weight and so easy to use. Glides through anything effortlessly! Washes off easy and have survived may washed in the dishwasher without any issues. Would highly recommend any Rada stainless steel knife!!
